2. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves graph theory and connectivity problems, which are important topics in discrete mathematics. 
3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with graph connectivity, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses emergency planning and sensitivity settings, which are relevant to social and information networks. 
5. cs.AL (Automata and Formal Languages) - The paper involves the design and analysis of algorithms, which is a key area of research in automata and formal languages.
